header.gameNote: SUMMIT LEAGUE MEN'S CHAMPIONSHIP - QUARTERFINALS AT SIOUX FALLS SD

article.headline: N. Dakota St. 83, Centenary 77
article.story: SIOUX FALLS, S.D. -- Brett Winkelman was 12-for-13 from the free throw line and scored 30 points Saturday as top-seed North Dakota State beat Centenary 83-77 to avoid the upset in the first round of the Summit League tournament. Ben Woodside added 23 points for the Bison. Woodside was 11-for-14 from the line and NDSU finished with a 28-12 advantage in free throw scoring. NDSU (24-6) blew a 19-point halftime lead before rallying to advance to Monday's semifinals where it will play the IUPUI-Southern Utah winner. Centenary (8-23) erased a 48-29 halftime deficit and took its first lead at 68-67 on Nick Stallings' free throw with 6:05 left. The Gents led 70-69 until Michael Tveidt's two free throws with 3:32 to play put the Bison back on top. NDSU scored all 14 points of its points from the free throw line in the last 3:32. Chase Adams scored 28 points and Stallings added 21 for Centenary.
